                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d333">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">360c.1121 Zarzycki, Stephen/3: Telegram (part
                    air)</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Poland</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Nielsen</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Warsaw</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-07-23T15:00:00+01:00"
                            >July 23, 1936—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received July 24—3:10 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>67. Complied with your telegram of July 18, 3 p.m., in a conversation yesterday
                    with Undersecretary of State.<note n="5" xml:id="d333fn5">Count Jan
                        Szembek.</note> Embassy has this noon been informed by Foreign Office that
                    the Minister for Finance<note n="6" xml:id="d333fn6">Eugenjusz Kwiatkowski, also
                        Vice Premier.</note> has called for July 29, and that he will personally
                    preside over a meeting of the chiefs of customs offices from all border
                    stations. Instructions already have been sent to border officials to administer
                    regulations less rigidly.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Nielsen</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
